nl.tue.multibrowsertest

Class MultiBrowserTester<ResultObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tue.multibrowsertest.MultiBrowserTester<ResultObject>
  • Type Parameters:
    ResultObject - The object that will be returned as the result of the test.

    public class MultiBrowserTester<ResultObject>
extends Object
    Test-class used to run a Selenium browser-test concurrently on multiple remote browsers. Using a given CapabilitiesProvider, a series of TestRunners are created which will concurrently invoke CrossBrowserTest.test(org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver, TestRunner) of a given test. Screenshots can be taken for each browser and compared to each other to ensure compatibility with all browsers. In order to keep everything as generic as possible, is ResultObject can be specified, that will be returned by the and in turn reported back for each test by this class. In most cases this will be a Boolean.
    Author:
    Lasse Blaauwbroek

        Retrieves the list of screenshots taken by the last test-run. Each screenshot taken by a test is an entry in the list. The entry is a mapping from a dimension to a mapping of browsers with that dimension to the screenshot resulting from that browser.

      • compareLastScreenshots

        public List<Map<org.openqa.selenium.Dimension,Boolean>> compareLastScreenshots()
        Compares the screenshots taken by the last test-run and returns the result. For each screenshot taken there is an entry in the returned list. Each entry is a mapping from a tested dimension to a boolean representing whether or not all browsers with that dimension returned an equal screenshot.
        Returns:
        The list
